&ndash; Note: This post is a personal opinion/analysis and cannot be considered legal advice. Feel free to reach out if you wish to discuss further or require advice for your specific situation! &ndash;
Over summer, ESMA updated its Q&amp;A on the AIFM Directive (EU Directive 2011/61/EU) with some new questions (and more importantly, answers) - including with respect to pre-marketing in a context of sub-threshold managers (AIFMs).
Summary: ESMA confirmed that sub-threshold managers are not subject to the obligation to notify pre-marketing (unless otherwise required by national rules).
